  "texts": [
    "The factor matrices are orthogonal, and the core tensor G encapsulates the principal interactions and serves as a compressed version of the original tensor [19].The fused tensor z m is decomposed into three matrices W a, W v, and W t, representing the acoustic, visual, and textual components, respectively, alongside a core matrix T c:T c = (G × 1 W a) × 2 W v × 3 W t(4)The core matrix T c not only encapsulates the essential content from the acoustic, visual, and textual components but also their intrinsic interrelations, while maintaining a lower data volume and dimensionality compared to the original fusion tensor z m.Multi-Modal Emotion Recognition Using Tensor Decomposition Fusion and Self-Super UNIMODAL TASKIn the evaluation of multimodal fusion algorithms, performance metrics play a critical role.",
    "These metrics enable the assessment of the efficacy of the algorithms in various contexts.",
    "The Tucker decomposition, in particular, is leveraged to transform the high-dimensional fusion tensor into a core tensor and associated matrices, significantly reducing the complexity of the multimodal data.",
    "As illustrated in Figure 3, The unimodal Latent Geometric (LG) framework is applied to extract the most informative features from each modality, subsequently represented by the core tensor C [20].",
    "The core tensor C is defined as:C p = N i=1 I(v i (s) > 0) • f g p • v i N i=1 I(v i (s) > 0)(5)C m = N i=1 I(v i (s) < 0) • f g m • v i N i=1 I(v i (s) < 0) (6)where I is an indicator function, v i (s) is the i-th scalar support vector, f g p and f g m are the positive and negative class centroids of the data distribution."
  ],
